{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"http://ghost.local:8000","title":"PSD SDC Toolkits","description":"PSD SDC Toolkits."}},"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Tags","date":null,"date_pretty":null,"path":null,"meta_title":"Using Tags in Ghost - Core Concepts","meta_description":"Discover how to use the primary taxonomy within Ghost for filtering and organising the relationships between your publication content.","image":null,"next":null,"sidebar":"concepts","toc":null,"keywords":["concepts","ghost","publishing","tags"]},"html":"<p>Tags are the primary taxonomy within Ghost for filtering and organising the relationships between your content.</p>\n<p>Right off the bat, probably the best way to think about tags in Ghost is like labels in GMail. Tags are a powerful, dynamic taxonomy which can be used to categorise content, control design, and drive automation within your site.</p>\n<h2 id=\"tag-types\"><a href=\"#tag-types\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tag types</h2>\n<p>Tags are much more than just simple keywords - there are several different ways of using them to accomplish a variety of use-cases.</p>\n<h3 id=\"regular-tag\"><a href=\"#regular-tag\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Regular tag</h3>\n<p>All tags come with their own data object and can have a title, description, image and meta data. Ghost Handlebars Themes will automatically generate tag archive pages for any tags which are assigned to active posts. For example all posts tagged with <code class=\"language-text\">News</code> will appear on <code class=\"language-text\">example.com/tag/news/</code>, as well as in the automatically generated XML sitemap.</p>\n<h3 id=\"primary-tag\"><a href=\"#primary-tag\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Primary tag</h3>\n<p>Ghost has a concept of <code class=\"language-text\">primary_tag</code>, used simply to refer to the very first tag which a post has. This is useful for when you want to return a singular, most-important tag rather than a full array of all tags assigned to a post.</p>\n<h3 id=\"internal-tag\"><a href=\"#internal-tag\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Internal tag</h3>\n<p>Tags which are prefixed by a <code class=\"language-text\">#</code> character, otherwise known as hashtags, are internal tags within Ghost - which is to say that they aren't rendered publicly. This can be particularly useful when you want to drive particular functionality based on a tag, but you don't necessarily want to output the tag for readers to see.</p>\n<h2 id=\"example-usage\"><a href=\"#example-usage\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Example usage</h2>\n<p>As a quick example of how you might use tags, let's look at a quick example of a Hollywood news site which is publishing a post about Ryan Reynolds being announced as the lead in a new movie called \"Son of Deadpool\".</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/35f9b/tags.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 17.744916820702404%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/d19d2/tags.webp 163w,\n/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/9c1cd/tags.webp 325w,\n/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/bc0ed/tags.webp 650w,\n/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/e5b2b/tags.webp 975w,\n/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/d43dc/tags.webp 1082w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/5e27a/tags.png 163w,\n/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/034ef/tags.png 325w,\n/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/59fd5/tags.png 650w,\n/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/d1e75/tags.png 975w,\n/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/35f9b/tags.png 1082w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/7d643f6962d23ff6a43ff023e5cd1c7c/59fd5/tags.png\"\n          alt=\"Tags\"\n          title=\"\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>Here the post has 4 tags:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Breaking news</code> - The <strong>primary tag</strong></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Ryan Reynolds</code> - A regular tag</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">New Releases</code> - A regular tag</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">#feature</code> - An internal tag</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The front-end of the site has configured a rotating banner on the homepage to pull the latest 3 posts from the <code class=\"language-text\">Breaking News</code> category and highlight them right at the top of the page with a <strong>Breaking News</strong> label beside the byline.</p>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">Ryan Reynolds</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">New Releases</code> tags generate archives so that readers can browse other stories in the same categories, as well as their own sitemaps.</p>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">#feature</code> tag is used by the front-end or theme-layer as a conditional flag for activating specific formatting. In this instance the Deadpool PR team have supplied some marketing material including a giant wallpaper image which would make a great background, so the post is tagged with <code class=\"language-text\">#feature</code> to push the post image to be full bleed and take over the whole page.</p>\n<p>You can see this use-case in action on the main Ghost blog. Here's <a href=\"/concepts/https://blog.ghost.org/image-galleries_zh_CN\">a regular post</a>, and here's a <a href=\"/concepts/https://blog.ghost.org/5_zh_CN\">#feature</a>. The design of the post reacts to the tags.</p>\n<h2 id=\"tag-archives\"><a href=\"#tag-archives\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Tag archives</h2>\n<p>All actively used public tags (so, those not prefixed with <code class=\"language-text\">#</code>) generate automatic tag archives within Ghost Handlebars Themes. Tag archives are automatically added to the Google XML Sitemap, and have their own pagination and RSS feeds.</p>\n<p>Here's an example of an <a href=\"/concepts/https://demo.ghost.io/tag/getting-started_zh_CN\">tag archive</a> in the default Ghost Theme:</p>\n<p><a href=\"/concepts/https://demo.ghost.io/tag/getting-started_zh_CN\"><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 63.68852459016393%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/301114e716fb4e6a40881f8d91790979/f1ac9/tag-archive.webp 163w,\n/static/301114e716fb4e6a40881f8d91790979/3a072/tag-archive.webp 325w,\n/static/301114e716fb4e6a40881f8d91790979/a5a3c/tag-archive.webp 650w,\n/static/301114e716fb4e6a40881f8d91790979/74922/tag-archive.webp 975w,\n/static/301114e716fb4e6a40881f8d91790979/f397c/tag-archive.webp 1220w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/301114e716fb4e6a40881f8d91790979/a23fd/tag-archive.jpg 163w,\n/static/301114e716fb4e6a40881f8d91790979/063f5/tag-archive.jpg 325w,\n/static/301114e716fb4e6a40881f8d91790979/0b121/tag-archive.jpg 650w,\n/static/301114e716fb4e6a40881f8d91790979/4dd9a/tag-archive.jpg 975w,\n/static/301114e716fb4e6a40881f8d91790979/b17ff/tag-archive.jpg 1220w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/301114e716fb4e6a40881f8d91790979/0b121/tag-archive.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Tag Archive\"\n          title=\"\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </span></a></p>\n<p>Tag archives are only generated for tags which are assigned to published posts, any other tags are not publicly visible.</p>\n<h2 id=\"sample-api-data\"><a href=\"#sample-api-data\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sample API data</h2>\n<p>Here's a sample tag object from the Ghost <a href=\"/concepts//api/content_zh_CN\">Content API</a>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json\"><pre class=\"language-json\"><code class=\"language-json\">tag<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"id\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"1239bbfe90a518a862677abc\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"name\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Getting Started\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"slug\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"getting-started\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"url\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"https://path.to/tag/getting-started/\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"feature_image\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token null\">null</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"visibility\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"public\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"meta_title\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token null\">null</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">\"meta_description\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token null\">null</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>","fields":{"slug":"/concepts/tags/"},"timeToRead":3,"excerpt":"Tags are the primary taxonomy within Ghost for filtering and organising the relationships between your content. Right off the bat, probablyâ€¦","fileAbsolutePath":"/Users/gavinwang/Documents/Working/codes/sdc_toolkits/content/concepts/tags.md"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/concepts/tags/"}}